I thought I was working

274
00:11:06,430 --> 00:11:08,060
With Ponyville's
best athlete!

275
00:11:08,830 --> 00:11:09,970
You are!

276
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:11,520
I'm okay!

277
00:11:11,730 --> 00:11:12,350
Really.

278
00:11:12,730 --> 00:11:14,110
I-I have an idea.

279
00:11:14,290 --> 00:11:15,230
Watch this.

280
00:11:16,020 --> 00:11:18,320
[ Grunting ]

281
00:11:18,590 --> 00:11:19,760
Ta-Da!

282
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:22,350
Oh. Maybe not.

283
00:11:22,570 --> 00:11:24,050
Okay, one more try.

284
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,440
I'm sure to get it
this time.

285
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:26,350
[ Grunts ]

286
00:11:26,690 --> 00:11:27,680
[ Groans ]

287
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:34,040
[ Chuckles nervously ]

288
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:34,970
Here I go.

289
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:38,210
Wait!

290
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:42,440
Appleja-a-a-a-ck!

291
00:11:42,670 --> 00:11:44,060
You're welcome!

292
00:11:47,690 --> 00:11:49,700
Aah! Unh!
[ Thud! ]

293
00:11:50,220 --> 00:11:51,360
Can I help you?

294
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:56,240
I think somepony else
needs your help.

295
00:11:56,380 --> 00:11:58,120
Applejack?
Yep.

296
00:12:04,430 --> 00:12:05,100
[ Thud! ]
Ow!

297
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:07,500
[ Ears ringing ]

298
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:08,980
Applejack,
can we talk?

299
00:12:09,530 --> 00:12:11,390
[ Ringing ]

300
00:12:11,970 --> 00:12:13,470
[ Muffled ]
Applejack, can we talk?

301
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,590
Can bees squawk?!

302
00:12:16,830 --> 00:12:18,210
I don't think so!

303
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,810
No. Can we talk?

304
00:12:20,050 --> 00:12:23,110
20 stocks?!
Bean or celery?

305
00:12:23,230 --> 00:12:25,740
No! I need
to talk to you!

306
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:28,130
You need to walk
to the zoo?!

307
00:12:28,270 --> 00:12:30,000
Well,
who's stoppin' you?!

308
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,760
I need to talk to you!

309
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:34,570
Oh! Well,
why didn't you say so?!

310
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,390
What you want
to talk about?!

311
00:12:36,510 --> 00:12:38,880
Rainbow Dash dropped in
to see me today.

312
00:12:38,970 --> 00:12:41,390
That's quite neighborly
of her!

313
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:43,960
Yes, except that
she crashed onto my balcony

314
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:45,840
After you launched her
into the air.

315
00:12:46,210 --> 00:12:47,410
Oh, yeah.

316
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:50,310
I wasn't feelin'
quite myself this mornin'.

317
00:12:50,590 --> 00:12:53,360
Because you're working too hard,
and you need help!

318
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:56,050
What? Kelp?
I don't need kelp.

319
00:12:56,390 --> 00:12:57,570
I don't even like seaweed.

320
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,740
Help!
You need HELP!!

321
00:13:00,210 --> 00:13:01,760
Nothin' doin',
Twilight.

322
00:13:01,850 --> 00:13:04,160
I'm gonna prove to you,
to everypony,

323
00:13:04,210 --> 00:13:06,300
That I can do this
on my own.

324
00:13:06,610 --> 00:13:07,440
[ Thud! ]
Ow!

325
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:08,620
[ Grunts ]

326
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:10,530
Now, if you'll excuse me,

327
00:13:10,670 --> 00:13:12,560
I got to go
help Pinkie Pie.

328
00:13:13,390 --> 00:13:14,530
[ Groans ]

329
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:19,500
Now, Pinkie Pie, are you sure
you're up for baking the muffins

330
00:13:19,530 --> 00:13:21,060
And running the store
this afternoon?

331
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:23,150
Yes, sirree bob,
mrs. Cake!

332
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:25,710
Plus, I have Ponyville's
prize pony to help me out.

333
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:28,630
Why, she's the best baker ever!
Right, Applejack?

334
00:13:28,770 --> 00:13:30,360
[ Echoing ] Applejack.

335
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:31,680
[ Rattle! ]

336
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:34,130
No? You're not
the best baker ever?

337
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:36,020
What? Oh, no!

338
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:38,110
I mean,
don't you fret.

339
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,570
I can bake anything
from fritters to Pies

340
00:13:40,590 --> 00:13:41,890
In the blink of an eye.

341
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:43,650
[ Chuckles ]
all right.

342
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:45,160
Well, see you later,
girls.

343
00:13:45,230 --> 00:13:46,170
[ Rattle! ]

344
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,470
Stop with the shakin'!
It's time to get bakin'!

345
00:13:50,620 --> 00:13:51,460
All righty.

346
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:52,800
I'll get the sugar
and the eggs.

347
00:13:52,870 --> 00:13:54,430
Can you get me
some chocolate chips?

348
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:56,930
Uh...what was that?

349
00:13:57,290 --> 00:14:00,670
[ Distorted ]
chocolate chips.

350
00:14:00,780 --> 00:14:02,290
Chips. Got it.

351
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,900
Tater chips.

352
00:14:03,990 --> 00:14:05,500
A little salty and dry.

353
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:06,820
Okeydokey.

354
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:09,130
What next?

355
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:11,130
[ Distorted ]
baking soda.

356
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:13,170
Soda? Perfect!

357
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,840
That'll get the tater chips
nice and wet.

358
00:14:17,830 --> 00:14:18,890
Now what?!

359
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,160
[ Normal voice ]
a cup of flour.

360
00:14:20,890 --> 00:14:22,240
A cup of sour?

361
00:14:22,620 --> 00:14:24,630
Well, lemons are sure sour.

362
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,530
One cup of sour comin' up.

363
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:29,250
Anything else, Pinkie?

364
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,310
One last thing --
Wheat germ.

365
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:33,110
Wheat worms?

366
00:14:33,310 --> 00:14:36,460
Oh, that must be fancy talk
for earthworms.

367
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:43,250
Now, that's gonna
be delicious!

368
00:14:43,970 --> 00:14:45,530
If you say so.

369
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:50,320
Free-Muffin-Sample
spectacular!

370
00:14:51,550 --> 00:14:53,550
Derpy: Muffins

371
00:14:55,180 --> 00:14:57,330
Yeah!
Muffin spectacles!

372
00:14:57,390 --> 00:14:58,940
Get 'em
while they're hot!

373
00:15:01,610 --> 00:15:03,100
We came
as soon as we heard.

374
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:04,880
Oh, thank you, Twilight.

375
00:15:05,050 --> 00:15:06,700
We need all the help
we can get.

376
00:15:07,110 --> 00:15:10,620
[ All groaning ]

377
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,500
Oh, no.
What happened?

378
00:15:13,630 --> 00:15:15,960
It was a mishap
with some of the baked goods.

379
00:15:16,570 --> 00:15:17,310
No!

380
00:15:17,570 --> 00:15:19,010
Not baked goods.

381
00:15:19,630 --> 00:15:20,910
Baked bads.

382
00:15:21,150 --> 00:15:21,760
Ugh!

383
00:15:22,910 --> 00:15:23,660
Applejack.

384
00:15:23,710 --> 00:15:24,780
Oh! Mmm!

385
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:26,000
Want one?

386
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:30,900
[ Grunts ]

387
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:32,320
[ Snores ]

388
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:33,730
What? Huh?

389
00:15:36,610 --> 00:15:38,350
[ Grunts ]

390
00:15:38,930 --> 00:15:40,320
Ohh! Unh!

391
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:41,790
[ Snoring lightly ]

392
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,610
Applejack,
we need to talk.

393
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:45,520
What?! Huh?!

394
00:15:46,060 --> 00:15:47,890
Oh, it's you, Twilight.

395
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,530
[ Yawning ] I know
what you're gonna say.

396
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,700
But the answer
is still no.

397
00:15:52,820 --> 00:15:55,650
Not to upset your apple cart,
but you need help.

398
00:15:55,810 --> 00:15:57,050
[ Sighs ]
hardy-Har.

399
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:59,840
[ Grunts ]
and, no, I don't.

400
00:15:59,980 --> 00:16:00,590
[ Grunts ]

401
00:16:00,730 --> 00:16:02,110
Here. Let me help.

402
00:16:02,210 --> 00:16:04,320
Help? No, thanks.

403
00:16:04,460 --> 00:16:05,640
[ Grunting ]

404
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:07,640
A little more.

405
00:16:08,530 --> 00:16:09,660
A little...

406
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,460
[ grunts ]

407
00:16:11,540 --> 00:16:12,270
There.

408
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:17,470
I'll prove that this apple
can handle these apples.

409
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:19,810
Come on [grunts] apples.

410
00:16:19,940 --> 00:16:22,690
[ Grunts ]
fall off! [ Grunts ]

411
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:24,940
A.J., I think
you're beating a dead...

412
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:26,430
tree.

413
00:16:28,170 --> 00:16:28,900
I knew that.

414
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:30,800
Actually, Applejack,

415
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:32,680
I had something else
to talk to you about.

416
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,830
I just came back from
Ponyville urgent care and --

417
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,490
You know,
I'm a little busy

418
00:16:36,510 --> 00:16:38,210
To get lectured
right now, Twilight.

419
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:40,130
If you'd just
let me help --
Ugh!

420
00:16:40,370 --> 00:16:42,450
No! No! No!

421
00:16:43,050 --> 00:16:45,640
How many times
do I got to say it?

422
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:48,490
I don't need no help
from nopony!

423
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:52,070
Ugh! That pony
is stubborn as a mule!

424
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:53,600
[ Mule brays ]
no offense.

425
00:16:54,420 --> 00:16:55,600
None taken.

426
00:16:58,460 --> 00:17:00,540
Fluttershy: oh, Applejack,
thank you so much

427
00:17:00,580 --> 00:17:01,950
For offering
your herding skills

428
00:17:01,970 --> 00:17:03,550
For the annual
rabbit roundup.

429
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:05,720
[ Sighs ]
why are we doing this?

430
00:17:05,890 --> 00:17:08,530
Well, lots of new baby bunnies
have been born,

431
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:11,480
So it's my job to get a count
of all the new families.

432
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:12,020
Fine.

433
00:17:12,110 --> 00:17:13,340
Can we just
get on with it?

434
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,090
Certainly, but remember,

435
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:17,570
These are bunnies
we're dealing with, not cows.

436
00:17:17,790 --> 00:17:20,160
They're a timid bunch
and need to be treated gently.

437
00:17:20,210 --> 00:17:23,710
I do not need any direction
on corrallin' critters.

438
00:17:23,930 --> 00:17:24,930
Right, Winona?!

439
00:17:25,010 --> 00:17:25,680
[ Barks ]

440
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:26,970
[ Bunnies sniffing ]

441
00:17:27,050 --> 00:17:28,660
Okay, little bunnies.

442
00:17:28,890 --> 00:17:31,650
I need you to all gather
here in the middle.

443
00:17:32,140 --> 00:17:34,050
That's right!
Let's go, bunnies!

444
00:17:34,170 --> 00:17:35,810
In the center!
Hop to it!

445
00:17:35,850 --> 00:17:36,530
[ Zip! ]

446
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:38,480
Swell.
Just swell.

447
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:42,720
Put 'em up, Winona!

448
00:17:42,990 --> 00:17:44,320
[ Barking ]

449
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:49,650
Applejack! Winona! Stop!

450
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:51,480
You're scaring them!

451
00:17:51,590 --> 00:17:52,820
We know
what we're doin'!

452
00:17:53,090 --> 00:17:54,590
Get along, little bunnies!

453
00:17:54,630 --> 00:17:55,480
[ Barking ]

454
00:17:57,150 --> 00:17:58,690
[ Growling ]

455
00:18:00,670 --> 00:18:01,770
Oh, no.

456
00:18:01,820 --> 00:18:03,200
[ Bunnies scream ]

457
00:18:06,220 --> 00:18:08,090
[ Rumbling ]

458
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:10,540
Stampede!

459
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:16,610
[ Indistinct shouting ]

460
00:18:25,650 --> 00:18:27,100
[ Moans ]

461
00:18:33,650 --> 00:18:35,690
[ Humming ]

462
00:18:35,790 --> 00:18:36,370
[ Gasps ]

463
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:40,150
The horror!
The horror!

464
00:18:40,220 --> 00:18:42,300
It was awful!
A disaster!

465
00:18:42,470 --> 00:18:44,190
A horrible,
horrible disaster!

466
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:46,320
[ Birds chirping ]

467
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:47,250
I don't get it.

468
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:49,660
Our gardens destroyed.

469
00:18:49,740 --> 00:18:51,430
Every last flower
devoured.

470
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:54,240
By -- By...them!

471
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,960
Fluttershy: oh, my!
Oh, please stop, little bunnies.

472
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:59,500
Oh, no!
Please, let's go home.

473
00:18:59,570 --> 00:19:01,350
No! Oh!
Oh, my goodness.

474
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:02,510
All right.

475
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:04,340
Enough is enough.

476
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:08,250
Must keep buckin'.

477
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:11,610
Just a few more.

478
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,860
Must finish harvestin'.

479
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:14,920
All right, Applejack,

480
00:19:15,180 --> 00:19:17,450
Your apple bucking hasn't
just caused you problems.

481
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:19,120
It's overpropelled
pegasus,

482
00:19:19,210 --> 00:19:20,810
Practically poisoned
plenty of ponies,

483
00:19:20,890 --> 00:19:23,070
And terrorized bushels of
brand-New bouncing baby bunnies.

484
00:19:23,250 --> 00:19:24,560
I don't care
what you say.

485
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,000
You need help.

486
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:27,320
[ Grunts ]

487
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,410
Ha! No, I don't.

488
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:32,080
Look, I did it.

489
00:19:32,860 --> 00:19:35,890
I harvested
the entire sweet apple acres

490
00:19:36,030 --> 00:19:37,200
Without your help.

491
00:19:38,060 --> 00:19:39,920
How do you like
them apples?

492
00:19:40,060 --> 00:19:43,490
Oh, how do you like
them apples?

493
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,420
[ Whimpering ]

494
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:51,200
[ Mumbling indistinctly ]

495
00:19:54,150 --> 00:19:55,500
Applejack?

496
00:19:56,170 --> 00:19:57,020
Applejack?

497
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:58,050
Huh?

498
00:19:58,170 --> 00:19:59,770
Oh, good.
You're okay.

499
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:02,310
Now, Applejack,
I completely respect

500
00:20:02,350 --> 00:20:03,470
The apple-Family ways.

501
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:06,040
You're always there
to help anypony in need.

502
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:09,020
So maybe you can put a little
of your stubborn pride aside

503
00:20:09,050 --> 00:20:10,860
And allow your friends
to help you.

504
00:20:11,750 --> 00:20:12,830
Okay, Twilight.

505
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:15,120
I am not taking no
for an answer. What?

506
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:16,930
Yes, Twilight.

507
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:18,490
Yes, please.

508
00:20:18,670 --> 00:20:20,330
I could really
use your help.

509
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:21,720
[ Chuckles ]

510
00:20:22,020 --> 00:20:23,210
[ Sighs ]

511
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:26,240
Twilight Sparkle:
"dear princess Celestia,

512
00:20:26,410 --> 00:20:29,640
"My friend Applejack is the best
friend a pony could ever have,

513
00:20:29,850 --> 00:20:32,080
"And she's always there
to help anypony.

514
00:20:32,290 --> 00:20:34,300
"The only trouble is,
when she needs help,

515
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:35,840
"She finds it hard to accept it.

516
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:38,930
"So while friendship is about
giving of ourselves to friends,

517
00:20:38,980 --> 00:20:41,630
"It's also about accepting
what our friends have to offer.

518
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,380
Your faithful student,
Twilight Sparkle."

519
00:20:44,590 --> 00:20:46,190
How about y'all
take a little break?

520
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:48,960
I got some fine apple juice
waitin' for you.

521
00:20:49,460 --> 00:20:49,920
[ Sighs ]

522
00:20:50,140 --> 00:20:52,620
Girls, I can't thank you enough
for this help.

523
00:20:53,150 --> 00:20:55,150
I was actin'
a bit stubborn.

524
00:20:55,210 --> 00:20:56,000
A bit?

525
00:20:56,170 --> 00:20:58,330
Okay, a might stubborn.

526
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,720
And I'm awful sorry.

527
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:04,300
Now, I know the town gave me
the prize pony award,

528
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:08,430
But the real award is
having you five as my friends.

529
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:10,060
[ Slurping ]

530
00:21:10,190 --> 00:21:13,770
Whew! That applebucking
sure made me hungry.

531
00:21:13,870 --> 00:21:15,690
And I've got
the perfect treat!

532
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:18,030
Ew! Spike,
I threw those away!

533
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:19,460
Where did you get them?

534
00:21:19,740 --> 00:21:20,790
From the trash!

535
00:21:21,170 --> 00:21:22,870
Ew!
Ew!Ew!
Ew!

536
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:25,240
Just a little nibble?

537
00:21:25,290 --> 00:21:26,380
Come on!

538
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:27,960
Ew! Gross!

539
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:29,250
Gross, Spike!

